        "timeEstimate": 10
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You draw in a slow breath, filling your lungs with the crisp air of Harrow's Hollow. The familiar scents of fresh bread, spring earth, and woodsmoke mingle in the square. Around you, the villagers' celebration shows no sign of fading; children dart between adults, clutching garlands and hero-tokens, while Elder Mirna exchanges fond words with her neighbors. Elen stands close, her expression softer than you've ever seen it. She watches the crowd, a hint of disbelief and gratitude in her eyes.\n\nElen leans in and speaks quietly, her voice just for you. \"It's strange, isn't it? To know you've done something that will be remembered. I always thought I'd just be another ranger patrolling the woods. Now... well, I suppose we'll see what comes next.\"\n\nAt the edge of the square, Elder Mirna rises from the fountain and approaches, her steps unhurried. She waits until you and Elen are ready, then addresses you both with a gentle, sincere smile. \"There is time yet for celebration, but I would not have the two of you slip away before we've spoken. Norn, Elen, will you join me inside the guardhouse for a moment? There are matters of reward, opportunity, and perhaps a few secrets still to share. The rest of the village can wait--you've earned that much.\"\n\nElen glances at you, her lips curving into a small smile. \"What do you say? Shall we see what the future holds? Or do you want to bask in the glory a little longer?\"",
